<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Basic channel

```
<$statewrap channels="active-tab" default-active-tab="home" instid="ex1">
  <$button><$action-statewrap-set channel="active-tab" value="home"/>Home</$button>
  <$button><$action-statewrap-set channel="active-tab" value="settings"/>Settings</$button>

  <$reveal stateTitle={{{[statewrap-ref[active-tab]]}}} type="match" text="home">
    Home content
  </$reveal>
  <$reveal stateTitle={{{[statewrap-ref[active-tab]]}}} type="match" text="settings">
    Settings content
  </$reveal>
</$statewrap>
```

!! Reactive rules — master/detail

```
<$statewrap channels="category item" instid="ex2">
  <$statewrap-rule when="category">
    <$action-statewrap-set channel="item" value=""/>
  </$statewrap-rule>

  <$list filter="Work Personal">
    <$button>
      <$action-statewrap-set channel="category" value=<<currentTiddler>>/>
      <<currentTiddler>>
    </$button>
  </$list>

  <%if [statewrap-get[category]!is[blank]]%>
    Category: <$text text={{{[statewrap-get[category]]}}}/>
  <%endif%>
</$statewrap>
```

!! Reading values in filters

```
<%if [statewrap-get[selected-project]!is[blank]]%>
  Project: <$text text={{{[statewrap-get[selected-project]]}}}/>
<%endif%>
```

!! Using statewrap-ref with components

`[statewrap-ref[channel]]` returns the state tiddler path, useful for widgets that expect a tiddler reference:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  sync-tiddler={{{[statewrap-ref[active-tab]]}}}
/>
```

!! Skipping rules with no-rules

```
<$action-statewrap-set channel="detail-tab" value="overview" no-rules="yes"/>
```

!! Reading a channel from outside the statewrap scope

`[statewrap-get[channel]]` requires a `<$statewrap>` ancestor in the widget tree. In contexts where no such ancestor exists (`\function` bodies, introspection templates rendered as page-template overlays, tool wikitext rendered detached via `$tw.fakeDocument`), use `[<instid>statewrap-lookup[channel]]` instead — it reads the state tiddler directly given the instid:

```
\function active-section() [[my-app]statewrap-lookup[section]]

<!-- equivalent to reading $:/state/rimir/statewrap/my-app/section -->
Current section: <$text text={{{[function[active-section]]}}}/>
```

This is particularly useful for LLM-facing templates and tools that need to report the current app state without being embedded in the app's render tree.

